    "summary": "As an art dealer with an academic background in history (BA) and art history (BA, MA), my focus is on researching, collecting, and selling artworks from the period 1850-1950. Bob Scholte Fine Art specializes in the market of Jan Mankes (1889-1920) and Nola Hatterman (1899-1984). I offer different services: my role involves assisting collectors in expanding their collections by sourcing desired artworks, offering deaccessioning guidance, serving as an intermediary, and conducting art historical research.\n\nAs the columnist for the well-known art magazine Tableau Fine Arts, I am responsible for writing the 'Art Hunt' article. In each edition, I take the reader into the life of an art dealer, such as attributing a painting to an Old Master, unravel the provenance of a painting or the search for extraordinary works of art. These artworks are subsequently available for purchase on my website. One such find is the oil painting Femme assise (1929) by the French cubist and theorist Andr\u00e9 Lhote, which garnered significant attention in the Dutch media, including various newspapers, radio, and the tv Talkshow Eva Jinek. Meanwhile, numerous artworks have been added to this list, solidifying my role as a full-time art dealer - one of the youngest in the Netherlands.\n\nExplore the collection, housing masterpieces that capture the transformative essence of this era. Appreciate the brush strokes of well-known artists such as Jan Toorop, Siebe ten Cate, Jan Mankes, Nola Hatterman, Jan Sluijters, and numerous others. Feel free to reach out if you're interested or visit my website: www.bobscholtefineart.nl",
